    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Layout: Chiefly 15 lines in two colums, with some single lines centered; catchwords every verso, lower left.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Script: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, vocalized.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Decoration: Polychrome and gold headpiece (f. 1v) with a gold floral and geometric pattern marginal fill over the page-opening (f. 1v-2r); textblock border-ruled in gold; columns and lines also ruled in gold; floral finispiece in gold (f. 31r); rubrications in red.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Origin: Copy completed by ʻAbd Allāh al-Wahbī (f. 31r); possibly 17th century.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="563" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
      <subfield code="a">Bound in red leather over pasteboard with black inlaid central mandorla painted with gold foliate design; gold tooled frame; marbled paper doublure and endleaves.</subfield>
    </datafield>
    <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
